The paper deals with auction design, which is a classic topic in game theory (cs.GT). The use of signaling schemes and the optimization of welfare involve techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of submodular function maximization, which is a common technique in economics and computer science for solving optimization problems (cs.EC). Finally, the paper deals with information theory and the communication of information, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
